` or for size, so I think using `$items.isEmpty()` is the better choice. I also wonder if the Velocity method parser accepts a boolean false output.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FkIKF5fEQWycqaHBgDtyW7ti|fc_0c8c976fed89f3ed0169f9aef7e6d08194af85e113215f6664", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.auto.value/auto-value/1.4.1/src/test/java/com_google_auto_value/auto_value/ReferenceNodeTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1043, "output": 938, "cacheRead": 17408, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 19389, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777970921783, "responseId": "resp_0c8c976fed89f3ed0169f9aeea3b488194bbc60955e0e5926c"}}
